fig values\n643:- [ ] Admin endpoints require operator auth (existing auth middleware or admin-only check)\n644:- [ ] Invalid config keys rejected (400)\n645:- [ ] Config change takes effect on next `game.settled` event (no restart needed)\n701:- [ ] `GET /challenges/mine` returns daily, weekly, and onboarding sections\n702:- [ ] Lazy assignment triggered on first call after daily/weekly reset\n703:- [ ] Response includes progress, target, status, reward, and reset countdown\n704:- [ ] Onboarding section shows locked steps (prerequisite not yet met) with `locked: true`\n705:- [ ] Onboarding section is `null` for players who completed all onboarding steps\n706:- [ ] `GET /points/mine` returns `{ balance, lifetimeEarned }`\n707:- [ ] `GET /points/mine/history` returns paginated point grant rows with source metadata and timestamps from `point_grants`\n708:- [ ] `GET /challenges/mine/history` returns paginated past completions\n709:- [ ] `GET /crates/mine` returns paginated crate drops with type, amount, timestamp, and payout status semantics (`pending` queued, `granted` applied, `failed` needs retry/manual review)\n710:- [ ] `GET /dogpile/current` returns active event with countdown to `ends_at`, or next scheduled event with countdown to `starts_at`\n711:- [ ] All endpoints require JWT auth (existing middleware)\n712:- [ ] All endpoints use standard error format (existing `errorResponse` helper)\n734:- [ ] All admin endpoints require operator-level auth\n735:- [ ] Campaign CRUD: create, update, toggle active. Cannot delete (soft-disable only).\n736:- [ ] Challenge CRUD: create, update, toggle active within a campaign\n737:- [ ] Dogpile scheduling: create events, cancel future events, cannot modify active events\n738:- [ ] Reward config: read all, update by key\n739:- [ ] Reward pool: read current balance, lifetime funded, lifetime paid\n878:[Omitted long matching line]\n882:[Omitted long matching line]","numLines":118}}
