{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019ega3ebEPf5RNSvJ7MKtjn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear understanding of the current state. I need to implement:\n\n1. Admin dogpile endpoints in `admin.ts`:\n   - `POST /admin/dogpile` — schedule event with starts_at, ends_at, multiplier, optional campaign_id — validate no overlap with existing non-cancelled events\n   - `PUT /admin/dogpile/:id` — cancel future/scheduled events — cannot modify active events\n   - `GET /admin/dogpile` — list all events with status filter\n\n2. Dogpile status worker: transitions `scheduled→active` when `now() >= starts_at` and `active→ended` when `now() >= ends_at`\n\n\n3. Integration tests to verify the endpoints and worker behavior, then I should review the spec's FR-6 section to ensure I'm covering all the dogpile requirements.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":140,"cache_read_input_tokens":66357,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":140},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d57cf433-e8fe-4f4f-ba7f-c634be571ed8","uuid":"7a34e4dc-8b22-4821-8c5a-57e0964b1f50"}
